</SO>
<CO>
   SUNW
</CO>
<IN>
STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK)
</IN>
<LP>
   Mountainview, Calif. -- Sun Microsystems Inc. said it
filed a registration statement with the Securities and
Exchange Commission covering a proposed offering of 5,938,834
new shares of common stock together with 1,061,166 shares to
be offered by certain selling shareholders.
   Sun said 5.6 million of the shares will be sold in the
United States by Goldman, Sachs &amp; Co., Salomon Brothers Inc.
and Dean Witter Reynolds Inc.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Another 1.4 million shares will be sold outside the U.S.
by an international syndicate managed by Goldman Sachs
International Ltd., Salomon Brothers International Ltd. and
Dean Witter Capital Markets International Ltd.
</TEXT>
